<div class="cms-copy-rsp" >
    
        <p>If you feel that your data has not been handled correctly, or you are unhappy with our response to any requests you have made to us regarding the use of your personal data, you have the right to lodge a complaint with the Information Commissionerâs Office.</p>
<p>You can contact them by calling <a href="tel:03031231113">0303 123 1113</a>.<br>
Or go online to <a href="http://www.ico.org.uk/concerns" target="_blank">www.ico.org.uk/concerns</a>&nbsp;(opens in a new window; please note we can&#39;t be responsible for the content of external websites)</p>
<p>If you are based outside the UK, you have the right to lodge your complaint with the relevant data protection regulator in your country of residence. Details can be found in Section 16.<br>
</p>

    
